'''Gonzalo Ariel Montiel''' (born 1 January 1997) is an Argentine professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as [[right-back]] for the [[Argentine Primera División]] club [[Club Atlético River Plate|River Plate]] and the [[Argentina national football team|Argentina national team]].

Montiel began his professional career with River Plate in 2016, playing 140 games and winning honours including the Argentine Primera División in [[2021 Argentine Primera División|2021]] and the [[Copa Libertadores]] in [[2018 Copa Libertadores|2018]]. In 2021, he signed for [[Sevilla FC|Sevilla]] for €11 million, and was loaned to English side [[Nottingham Forest F.C.|Nottingham Forest]] for the 2023–24 season before returning to Seville for another year. Then, four years after his departure from Argentina, Montiel returned in January 2025 to River Plate.

Montiel made his senior international debut for Argentina in 2019. He was a part of the squads that won the [[Copa América]] in [[2021 Copa América|2021]] and [[2024 Copa América|2024]] and the [[FIFA World Cup]] in [[2022 FIFA World Cup|2022]], scoring the winning penalty in the [[Penalty shoot-out (association football)|shoot-out]] of the latter [[2022 FIFA World Cup final|final]].

== Club career ==

=== River Plate ===
[[File:Palestino - River Plate 20190424 05.jpg|upright|thumb|left|Montiel playing for [[Club Atlético River Plate|River Plate]] in 2019]]

Born in [[González Catán]], [[Buenos Aires Province]], Montiel was a product of the [[Club Atlético River Plate]] academy. In October 2015, manager [[Marcelo Gallardo]] called the 18-year-old up for the first time for an [[Argentine Primera División]] game at [[Defensa y Justicia]]; he was unused in the 1–0 loss on 15 October.<ref>{{cite news |title=Gallardo quiere confiar en una defensa joven ante Defensa y Justicia|trans-title=Gallardo wants to trust a young defender against Defensa y Justicia|url=https://www.lanacion.com.ar/deportes/futbol/gallardo-quiere-confiar-en-una-defensa-joven-ante-defensa-y-justicia-nid1835873/ |access-date=20 December 2022 |work=[[La Nación]] |date=12 October 2015 |language=Spanish}}</ref> He made his debut on 30 April 2016 in his one appearance of [[2016 Argentine Primera División|that season]], as a half-time substitute for [[Pablo Carreras]] in a goalless draw at home to [[Club Atlético Vélez Sarsfield]]; Gallardo had made 11 changes to his team with an eye to a [[Copa Libertadores]] second leg against [[C.S.D. Independiente del Valle]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Montiel: cinco años de evolución|trans-title=Montiel: five years of evolution |url=https://www.ole.com.ar/river-plate/montiel-debut-anos-river-evolucion_0_ugz4eanw3.html |access-date=20 December 2022 |work=[[Olé (sports newspaper)|Olé]] |date=2 May 2021 |language=Spanish}}</ref>

Montiel played four league matches the 2016–17 season. On 30 October, he was sent off in a 2–2 draw at [[Arsenal de Sarandí]].<ref>{{cite news |title=River igualó en Sarandí|trans-title=River matched in Sarandí|url=https://www.eltribuno.com/jujuy/nota/2016-10-31-1-30-0-river-igualo-en-sarandi |access-date=20 December 2022 |work=El Tribuno |date=31 October 2016 |language=Spanish}}</ref> He lifted the [[Copa Argentina]] trophy after playing all the matches from the last 16 to the [[2017 Copa Argentina Final|final]], in which his team beat [[Atlético Tucumán]].<ref name=copa17>{{cite news |last1=Balbi Vignolo |first1=Juan Patricio |title=Una gran sonrisa para terminar el año: River derrotó a Atlético Tucumán y volvió a conquistar la Copa Argentina|trans-title=A big smile to end the year: River defeated Atlético Tucumán and conquered the Copa Argentina again |url=https://www.lanacion.com.ar/deportes/futbol/river-atletico-tucuman-copa-argentina-el-equipo-de-gallardo-busca-defender-el-titulo-frente-al-decano-nid2089914/ |access-date=20 December 2022 |work=La Nación |date=10 December 2017 |language=Spanish}}</ref> He played in the [[2017 Copa Libertadores]], scoring a goal and assisting three, playing every minute from the quarter-finals to the semi-finals, where River Plate were defeated by [[Club Atlético Lanús]]; his first career goal came on 1 November in a 4–2 loss at Lanús.<ref>{{cite news |title=Lanús logró una remontada colosal y se metió en la final de la Libertadores|trans-title=Lanús achieved a colossal comeback and put themselves in the Libertadores final |url=https://www.eldia.com/nota/2017-11-1-4-41-36-lanus-logro-una-remontada-colosal-y-se-metio-en-la-final-de-la-libertadores-deportes |access-date=20 December 2022 |work=[[El Día (La Plata)|El Día]] |date=1 November 2017 |language=Spanish}}</ref>

In the 2017–18 season, Montiel played 35 matches, fifteen of them coming in the league. He made 14 appearances he made as the team lifted the Copa Libertadores at the [[Santiago Bernabéu Stadium]] against [[Superclásico]] rivals [[Boca Juniors]].<ref name=lib>{{cite news |last1=Ouzia |first1=Malik |title=River Plate win 2018 Copa Libertadores: Stunning Juan Quintero goal downs Boca Juniors at Santiago Bernabeu |url=https://www.standard.co.uk/sport/football/river-plate-win-2018-copa-libertadores-stunning-juan-quintero-goal-downs-boca-juniors-at-santiago-bernabeu-a4012606.html |access-date=20 December 2022 |work=[[Evening Standard]] |date=9 December 2018}}</ref> Playing five matches in the Copa Argentina, the team were eliminated on penalties in the semi-finals against [[Club de Gimnasia y Esgrima La Plata]]. The team secured a double that season as they beat Boca  in the [[Supercopa Argentina]].

The following season, Montiel played 12 matches in the league without being substituted. For the second season in a row, Montiel reached the Copa Libertadores final after twelve matches; however, River Plate would be defeated by [[CR Flamengo]]. He won the Copa Argentina once more as River beat Central Córdoba - he played every minute in the cup run. After winning last season's Copa Libertadores, River contested the [[FIFA Club World Cup]] where they finished third. An injury prevented him from playing in the Super Cup. After recovering, he returned to contest the Recopa as River overcame a 1–0 first-leg defeat to win the trophy with a 3–0 win against Club Athletico Paranaense.<ref name="SW"/>

On 20 February 2021, Montiel scored his first league goal for River, a [[Penalty kick (association football)|penalty]] in a 3–0 win against [[Rosario Central]] in the first game at the [[Estadio Monumental (Buenos Aires)|Estadio Monumental]] after a six-month renovation.<ref>{{cite news |title=En su regreso al Estadio Monumental, River jugó un gran partido y goleó a Rosario Central|trans-title=On their return to the Estadio Monumental, River played a great game and thrashed Rosario Central |url=https://www.infobae.com/deportes/2021/02/20/en-su-vuelta-al-monumental-river-buscara-levantar-ante-rosario-central-hora-tv-y-formaciones/ |access-date=20 December 2022 |publisher=Infobae |date=20 February 2021 |language=Spanish}}</ref>

=== Sevilla ===
On 13 August 2021, [[La Liga]] club [[Sevilla FC]] signed Montiel on a five-year deal for €11 million. Manager [[Julen Lopetegui]] signed him to compete with club icon [[Jesús Navas]] at right back after the exit of [[Aleix Vidal]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Oficial: Gonzalo Montiel ficha por el Sevilla|trans-title=Official: Gonzalo Montiel signs for Sevilla |url=https://www.marca.com/futbol/sevilla/2021/08/13/61169c1aca47418e3d8b45e6.html |access-date=20 December 2022 |work=[[Marca (newspaper)|Marca]] |date=13 August 2021 |language=Spanish}}</ref> He made his debut on 14 September in a [[UEFA Champions League]] group stage 1–1 home draw against [[FC Red Bull Salzburg]], replacing Navas for the last three minutes.<ref>{{cite news |title=Reparto de puntos en el empate a uno entre Sevilla y Red Bull Salzburgo|trans-title=Points shared in the one-one draw between Sevilla and Red Bull Salzburg |url=https://www.infobae.com/america/agencias/2021/09/13/sevilla-recibira-a-red-bull-salzburgo-por-la-fecha-1-del-grupo-g/ |access-date=20 December 2022 |publisher=Infobae |date=13 September 2021 |language=Spanish}}</ref> Eight days later, he made his league bow by starting against [[Valencia CF]] at the [[Ramón Sánchez Pizjuán Stadium]], scoring in the 15th minute of a 3–1 win before making way for Navas before the hour.<ref>{{cite news |title=Con goles del Papu Gómez y Montiel, el Sevilla derrotó al Valencia y sueña con dar pelea en la Liga de España |trans-title=With goals from Papu Gómez and Montiel, Sevilla defeated Valencia and dream of fighting for the Spanish League|url=https://www.infobae.com/america/deportes/espn/2021/09/22/con-goles-del-papu-gomez-y-montiel-el-sevilla-derroto-al-valencia-y-suena-con-dar-pelea-en-la-liga-de-espana/ |access-date=20 December 2022 |publisher=Infobae |date=22 September 2021 |language=Spanish}}</ref>

Montiel was [[Ejection (sports)|sent off]] on 6 November 2022 in a 1–1 [[Seville derby]] draw at [[Real Betis]] for a 38th-minute foul on [[Álex Moreno (footballer)|Álex Moreno]].<ref>{{cite news |last1=Lowe |first1=Sid |title=Red cards, a rocket and a ruckus: Seville derby ends in glorious chaos |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2022/nov/07/red-cards-a-rocket-and-a-ruckus-seville-derby-ends-in-glorious-chaos |access-date=20 December 2022 |work=[[The Guardian]] |date=7 November 2022}}</ref> On 31 May 2023, he scored the winning penalty in the [[2023 UEFA Europa League final|Europa League final]] against [[A.S. Roma|Roma]] in a 4–1 victory in the penalty shootouts after a 1–1 draw, which secured their seventh title in the competition.<ref name="auto1"/>

====Loan to Nottingham Forest====
On 23 August 2023, Montiel signed for [[Premier League]] club [[Nottingham Forest F.C.|Nottingham Forest]] on a season-long loan with the option to make the move permanent. He became the third Argentine in history to sign with the club.<ref>{{Cite news |title=Forest sign World Cup winner Montiel on loan |language=en-GB |work=BBC Sport |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/66600014 |access-date=2023-08-23}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Gonzalo Montiel da el salto a la Premier League |trans-title=Gonzalo Montiel makes the leap to the Premier League|url=https://onefootball.com/es/noticias/gonzalo-montiel-da-el-salto-a-la-premier-league-38089678 |access-date=24 August 2023 |publisher=Santa Fe Deportivo |date=23 August 2023 |language=Spanish}}</ref>

====Return to Sevilla====
After one season in the Premier League, Montiel returned to Sevilla after completing his loan spell for Nottingham Forest after playing 802 minutes for the English team. Forest had shown interest in signing him permanently, as well as fellow English side [[Everton FC]] and the Dutch team [[Feyenoord]], but ultimately Montiel returned to Spain.<ref>{{cite web| url=https://www.msn.com/en-gb/sport/fifa_world_cup/everton-join-race-for-sevillas-gonzalo-montiel/ar-AA1puFLI?ocid=BingNewsVerp| website=msn.com| title= Everton Join Race for Sevilla's Gonzalo Montiel| access-date =13 September 2024}}</ref><ref>{{cite web| url=https://www.marca.com/futbol/sevilla/2024/09/12/66e2b79346163fdd3d8b45c3.html| website=marca.com| title= Montiel, el 'fichaje' inesperado | trans-title=Montiel, the unexpected 'fixing' | language=es| date= 12 September 2024 }}</ref>

===Return to River Plate===
During the European winter club transfer period, Montiel was sold from Seville in January 2025 to his former club River Plate for a fee of $4.5 million, with a potential extra $500,000 for performance based results. His contract is until December 2028. He returned to his first club where he made 140 appearances with 6 goals from his debut in 2016.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.beinsports.com/en-us/soccer/liga-profesional-argentina/articles-video/gonzalo-montiel-reportedly-set-to-return-to-river-plate-2025-01-13|website=beinsports.com|title=Gonzalo Montiel Reportedly Set to Return to River Plate|date=13 January 2025}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.tribalfootball.com/article/soccer-laliga-sevilla-selling-montiel-to-river-plate-4bacd5d9-7e84-4c51-9e44-55d24d6a4cdf|website=tribalfootball.com|title=Sevilla selling Montiel to River Plate|date=14 January 2025}}</ref>

==International career==
[[File:Argentina 3-3 Francia - Copa Mundial 2022 - Montiel patea el penal de la victoria.jpg|thumb|Montiel scoring the winning penalty against France in the [[2022 FIFA World Cup final|2022 FIFA World Cup Final]]]]In March 2019, [[Argentina national football team|Argentina]] manager [[Lionel Scaloni]] called up Montiel as one of ten domestic-based players for [[Exhibition game|friendlies]] against [[Venezuela national football team|Venezuela]] and [[Morocco national football team|Morocco]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Los diez convocados por Scaloni de la Superliga |trans-title=The ten Superliga players called up by Scaloni |url=https://ar.marca.com/claro/futbol/seleccion-argentina/2019/03/07/5c81419d22601dde6a8b45a6.html |access-date=20 December 2022 |work=Marca |date=7 March 2019 |language=Spanish |archive-date=20 December 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221220202701/https://ar.marca.com/claro/futbol/seleccion-argentina/2019/03/07/5c81419d22601dde6a8b45a6.html |url-status=dead }}</ref> He made his debut on 22 March against Venezuela at the [[Metropolitano Stadium]] in [[Madrid]], playing the entirety of a 3–1 loss.<ref>{{cite news |last1=McTear |first1=Euan |title=More Wanda Metropolitano misery for Argentina on Messi's return |url=https://www.marca.com/en/football/international-football/cronica/2019/03/22/5c9560c6ca4741d7198b4615.html |access-date=20 December 2022 |work=Marca |date=22 March 2019}}</ref>

On 11 June 2021, Montiel was one of the 28-man squad announced by Argentina for the [[2021 Copa América]] tournament.<ref>{{cite news |title=Argentina national team squad Copa America 2021: selected players, absences... |url=https://en.as.com/en/2021/07/10/soccer/1625909611_909521.html |access-date=20 December 2022 |work=[[Diario AS]] |date=10 July 2021}}</ref> He played four of the seven matches played by the  team in the tournament including the [[2021 Copa América Final|final]] victory, which he had to complete with a bleeding ankle as a result of a tackle from [[Fred (footballer, born 1993)|Fred]] in the first half of the game.<ref name=copa21>{{cite web|last1=Armen Graham|first1=Bryan|url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/live/2021/jul/10/argentina-v-brazil-copa-america-final-live |title=Argentina 1–0 Brazil: Copa América final – as it happened |website=The Guardian |date=10 July 2021 }}</ref>

In November 2022, Montiel was named in the final squad for the [[2022 FIFA World Cup]] in Qatar.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Lea |first1=Greg |title=Argentina World Cup 2022 squad: Lionel Scaloni's full team |url=https://www.fourfourtwo.com/features/argentina-world-cup-2022-squad-players-line-up-qatar |access-date=20 December 2022 |work=[[FourFourTwo]] |date=18 December 2022}}</ref> During the tournament, he played against [[Mexico national football team|Mexico]] (as a starter, he was subbed out in the 63rd minute), [[Australia men's national soccer team|Australia]] (subbed in at the 80th minute), the [[Netherlands national football team|Netherlands]] (subbed in at the 106th minute, in extra time), and the [[2022 FIFA World Cup final|final]] against [[France national football team|France]] (when he was subbed in at the 91st minute). In the final, he conceded a penalty late in extra time after a handball. [[Kylian Mbappé]] then scored to make it 3-3, taking the final to a penalty shootout. After [[Kingsley Coman]] and [[Aurélien Tchouaméni]] missed their penalties, Montiel scored the tournament-winning penalty kick for Argentina in a 4–2 victory.<ref name=wc22>{{cite web |last=Burton |first=Chris |url=https://www.goal.com/en-us/news/watch-montiel-wins-shootout-messi-argentina-world-cup-final-france/bltadcb447f18994d35 |title=WATCH: Montiel wins shootout for Messi & Argentina after thrilling World Cup final clash with France |website=[[Goal.com]] |date=18 December 2022 }}</ref>

In June 2024, Montiel was included in Lionel Scaloni's final 26-man Argentina squad for the [[2024 Copa América]], also won by Argentina.<ref>{{Cite news |date=15 June 2024 |title=Lionel Scaloni dio a conocer la lista de la Selección argentina para la Copa América 2024 |url=https://tn.com.ar/deportes/futbol/2024/06/15/lionel-scaloni-dio-a-conocer-la-lista-de-la-seleccion-argentina-para-la-copa-america-2024/?gad_source=1&gclid=CjwKCAjwqf20BhBwEiwAt7dtdeK13_I24H4iqEBua7UtmDLn6_x-FfDm-gzEseLS8vJCnOlmjC3PlBoCHEwQAvD_BwE |access-date=23 July 2024 |work=Todo Noticias}}</ref>

==Personal life==
Montiel is from the [[Greater Buenos Aires]] area. His cousin, [[Santiago Montiel]], is also a footballer.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2022-02-08 |title=Santiago Montiel, primo de Gonzalo, muy cerca de marcharse libre de River a otro club de Primera División - TyC Sports |url=https://www.tycsports.com/river-plate/river-santiago-montiel-primo-de-gonzalo-muy-cerca-de-marcharse-libre-a-otro-club-de-primera-division-id410396.html |access-date=2025-10-03 |website=www.tycsports.com |language=es-AR}}</ref>

===False abuse allegations===
In June 2023, [[Mundo Deportivo]] reported that Argentine police had charged Montiel with sexual abuse in relation to an alleged incident on 1 January 2019, despite Montiel denying the allegations.<ref>{{cite news |title=Sevilla star Gonzalo Montiel faces sexual abuse charge plus uncertain future at La Liga club |url=https://www.planetsport.com/soccer/news/sevilla-star-gonzalo-montiel-faces-sexual-abuse-charge-plus-uncertain-future-club|website=planetsport.com |access-date=13 September 2024| date=17 June 2023}}</ref> Later in 2024, Montiel was ordered by a judge to undergo two separate psychiatric evaluations in Argentina. Yet, his lawyer asserted there was no evidence or testimony relating Montiel to the case, and expects it to be dismissed.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.footboom1.com/en/news/football/1843355-montiel-undergoes-second-psychological-evaluation-in-sexual-abuse-case|website=footboom1.com|title=Montiel Undergoes Second Psychological Evaluation in Sexual Abuse Case|date=20 September 2024}}</ref> Then, in due process, Montiel was acquitted of the sexual assault charge when the accusation was deemed to be "totally false". The case was dismissed in court during December 2024.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://sports.yahoo.com/totally-false-accusation-sevilla-defender-092400618.html?fr=sycsrp_catchall|website=sports.yahoo.com|title=“A totally false accusation” – Sevilla defender acquitted of sexual assault charge|date=31 December 2024}}</ref>

